comments: Westbrook (LAC) moves laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and initiates body contact that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Westbrook (LAC) absorbs the contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and brings his left hand to the ball and dislodges it during Gilgeous-Alexander's gather.
Leonard (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he becomes imminently legal as the ball is touched by a defender.
Westbrook (LAC) steps into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Westbrook (LAC) firms up in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Batum's (LAC) perimeter shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) does not step out of bounds as he saves the ball on the baseline.
Joe (OKC) legally contests Gordon's (LAC) perimeter shot attempt.

Joe (OKC) firms up in Leonard's (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
Gordon (LAC) absorbs the marginal contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) off-arm comes out slightly as he comes together with Gordon (LAC) during the drive. The contact on the play is marginal.
Gordon (LAC) lowers his right arm down and avoids making arm contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during his contest of the shot attempt in the paint.
Morris Sr. (LAC) does not deliver illegal contact when setting the screen on Dort (OKC).
Batum (LAC) lightly brushes Dort's (OKC) side as he slips the pick. The contact on the play is marginal.
Joe (OKC) lowers his right hand down and marginal body contact occurs with Batum (LAC) during his layup attempt at the basket.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Batum's (LAC) layup attempt at the basket.
Morris Sr. (LAC) and Wiggins (OKC) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Gordon (LAC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Morris Sr. (LAC) makes marginal contact to Joe's (OKC) arm after the release of his jump shot.
Dort (OKC) and Westbrook (LAC) make simultaneous contact with the ball and the ensuing body contact is incidental.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Westbrook (LAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Multiple angles reviewed. There is no clear and conclusive video evidence that shows Dort (OKC) makes last contact with the ball instead of Westbrook. Possession is properly retained by Oklahoma City.
